com.amplifyframework.core.model.temporal

Class Temporal.Timestamp

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amplifyframework.core.model.temporal.Temporal.Timestamp
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Temporal.Timestamp>
    Enclosing class:
    Temporal

    public static final class Temporal.Timestamp
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Temporal.Timestamp>
    The Temporal.Timestamp scalar type represents the number of seconds that have elapsed since 1970-01-01T00:00Z. Timestamps are serialized and deserialized as numbers. Negative values are also accepted and these represent the number of seconds til 1970-01-01T00:00Z.

      • Timestamp

        public Timestamp(long timeSinceEpoch,
                 java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Constructs a new Temporal.Timestamp, as an amount of time since the UNIX epoch.
        Parameters:
        timeSinceEpoch - An amount of time that has elapsed since the UNIX epoch, for example: 1_588_703_119L seconds. The unit for this value must be passed in the second argument.
        timeUnit - The unit in which the first argument is expressed. For example, if the first argument is 1_588_703_119L, that would represent the number of seconds between the UNIX epoch and Tuesday, May 5, 2020 6:25:19 PM in GMT.

      • Timestamp

        public Timestamp(java.util.Date date)
        Constructs an Temporal.Timestamp from a Date.
        Parameters:
        date - A date, that will be interrogated for the current UNIX time; any sub-second precision contained in the Date will be discarded.
